Date: Mon, 30 Dec 2013 20:57:28 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] Fix prototype of debugCallbackWrap

Declaration in src/OpenGl/OpenGl_glext.h is:

  typedef void (APIENTRY *GLDEBUGPROCARB)(GLenum source,GLenum type,GLuint id,GLenum severity,GLsizei length,const GLchar *message,GLvoid *userParam);

OCCT 6.7.0 ships an updated version of glext.h, which has a different
signature (with respect to the last argument).  So maybe this change
will be reverted if glext.h is updated.
---
 src/OpenGl/OpenGl_Context.cxx | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

Index: oce/src/OpenGl/OpenGl_Context.cxx
===================================================================
--- oce.orig/src/OpenGl/OpenGl_Context.cxx
+++ oce/src/OpenGl/OpenGl_Context.cxx
@@ -592,7 +592,7 @@ static void APIENTRY debugCallbackWrap(u
                                        unsigned int theSeverity,
                                        int          /*theLength*/,
                                        const char*  theMessage,
-                                       const void*  theUserParam)
+                                       void*  theUserParam)
 {
   OpenGl_Context* aCtx = (OpenGl_Context* )theUserParam;
   aCtx->PushMessage (theSource, theType, theId, theSeverity, theMessage);
